---

<MainLayout
  title="Storm Damage Roof Repair in Temple, Killeen & Central Texas | Lone Ranger Roofing"
  description="Storm damage to your roof? Lone Ranger Roofing handles the repair and walks you through the insurance claim from start to finish. Serving Temple, Killeen, and Central Texas."
  darkHero={true}
>

  <!-- ===================== HERO ===================== -->
  <section class="relative min-h-[65vh] flex items-center bg-brand-900 overflow-hidden -mt-28">
    <div class="absolute inset-0">
      <img
        src="/storm-damage.webp"
        alt="Storm damage roof repair — Temple and Killeen TX"
        class="w-full h-full object-cover"
      />
      <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-r from-brand-900 via-brand-900/85 to-brand-900/30"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="relative z-10 container mx-auto px-4 pt-20 pb-28">
      <div class="max-w-2xl">
        <p class="text-gold-400 font-bold text-sm uppercase tracking-widest mb-4">Residential Roofing &rsaquo; Storm Damage Repair</p>
        <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-black text-white leading-tight mb-6">
          Storm Damage Roof Repair in Temple, Killeen &amp; Central Texas
        </h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-gray-200 leading-relaxed mb-8">
          Hail. Wind. Heavy rain. The occasional flying pig. Whatever hit your roof, Lone Ranger Roofing will get out there fast, assess the full damage, and handle everything from emergency repairs to insurance claims.
        </p>
        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4">
          <a href="/contact" class="bg-accent-600 hover:bg-accent-700 text-white font-black px-8 py-4 rounded-lg text-sm uppercase tracking-wide transition-colors text-center shadow-lg">
            Schedule Free Inspection
          </a>
          <a href="tel:+12543001413" class="border-2 border-white/50 hover:border-white text-white font-bold px-8 py-4 rounded-lg text-sm uppercase tracking-wide transition-colors text-center hover:bg-white/10">
            Call (254) 300-1413
          </a>
        </div>

        <!-- Trust bar -->
        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-x-6 gap-y-3 mt-10">
          {[
            'Fast Storm Response',
            'Insurance Claim Help',
            'Material + Labor Warranty',
          ].map(t => (
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2 text-gray-300 text-sm">
              <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-gold-400 flex-shrink-0" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
                <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd"/>
              </svg>
              {t}
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===================== INSURANCE SECTION ===================== -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-white overflow-hidden">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4">
      <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center max-w-6xl mx-auto">

        <!-- Text side -->
        <div class="order-1">
          <p class="text-accent-600 font-bold text-sm uppercase tracking-widest mb-3">Insurance Claim Help</p>
          <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-black text-brand-900 mb-6">
            Most Homeowners Leave Money on the Table After a Storm. We Make Sure You Don't.
          </h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            When a storm damages your roof and you file a claim, your insurance company sends an adjuster to assess the damage. That adjuster works for the insurance company — not for you. Their job is to minimize the payout. If they miss something, you pay for it out of pocket.
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-8">
            Lone Ranger Roofing specializes in storm damage claims. We know what adjusters look for, what they overlook, and how to document the full scope of damage so your claim reflects what actually happened to your roof. We walk you through every step of the process — from the initial inspection to final approval — so you're not navigating it alone.
          </p>

          <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
            {[
              { stat: '100%', label: 'Damage Documented' },
              { stat: 'We Fight', label: 'Low Estimates' },
              { stat: '100s', label: 'Claims Handled' },
            ].map(item => (
              <div class="text-center border-t-2 border-accent-600 pt-4">
                <p class="text-brand-900 font-black text-xl leading-none mb-1">{item.stat}</p>
                <p class="text-gray-500 text-xs leading-snug">{item.label}</p>
              </div>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Checklist side -->
        <div class="relative order-2">
          <img
            src="/home-storm-damage-repair.webp"
            alt="Storm damage roof inspection — Bell County Texas"
            class="w-full h-[480px] object-cover rounded-2xl shadow-xl"
          />
          <div class="absolute bottom-6 right-6 bg-brand-900 text-white rounded-xl p-5 max-w-[220px] shadow-xl border border-white/10" style="align-self: end;">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-gold-400 mb-3" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M12 9v3.75m-9.303 3.376c-.866 1.5.217 3.374 1.948 3.374h14.71c1.73 0 2.813-1.874 1.948-3.374L13.949 3.378c-.866-1.5-3.032-1.5-3.898 0L2.697 16.126zM12 15.75h.007v.008H12v-.008z"/>
            </svg>
            <p class="text-gold-400 font-bold text-xs uppercase tracking-widest mb-3">What Adjusters Commonly Miss</p>
            <ul class="space-y-1.5">
              {[
                'Hail hits on flashing and vents',
                'Granule loss not visible from ground',
                'Damaged ridge caps',
                'Soft spots in decking',
                'Wind-lifted shingles that look intact from street level',
              ].map(item => (
                <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-brand-200 text-xs leading-snug">
                  <svg class="w-3 h-3 text-accent-600 flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
                    <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd"/>
                  </svg>
                  {item}
                </li>
              ))}
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===================== HOW IT WORKS ===================== -->
  <section class="relative py-24 bg-brand-900 text-white overflow-hidden">
    <div class="absolute inset-0">
      <img
        src="/home-gallery1.webp"
        alt="Lone Ranger Roofing crew at work"
        class="w-full h-full object-cover opacity-15"
      />
      <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-b from-brand-900/95 via-brand-900/80 to-brand-900/95"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="relative z-10 container mx-auto px-4 max-w-6xl">
      <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-14 items-center">

        <!-- Left: copy -->
        <div>
          <p class="text-gold-400 font-bold text-sm uppercase tracking-widest mb-3">How It Works</p>
          <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-black mb-6">
            How Lone Ranger Handles Storm Damage
          </h2>
          <p class="text-brand-200 leading-relaxed">
            We move fast after a storm. Here's what the process looks like from your first call to a finished roof.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Right: interactive step accordion -->
        <div class="space-y-2" id="steps-list">
          {[
            { n: '01', title: 'Free Roof Inspection & Damage Assessment', detail: 'We get eyes on your roof fast and document every inch of damage — the kind adjusters miss and the kind they try to minimize.' },
            { n: '02', title: 'Full Documentation for Your Insurance Claim', detail: 'We photograph, measure, and report the full scope of damage so your claim reflects what the storm actually did.' },
            { n: '03', title: 'We Meet the Adjuster On-Site If Needed', detail: 'If the adjuster needs to see the damage firsthand, we\'re there. We present our documentation and advocate for the full payout.' },
            { n: '04', title: 'Emergency Tarping or Leak Repair While You Wait on Approval', detail: 'We don\'t leave your home exposed. If you need immediate protection, we\'ll tarp the affected area to stop further water intrusion while the claim processes.' },
            { n: '05', title: 'Full Repair or Replacement Once Claim Is Approved', detail: 'One crew. One day. Done right. We complete the full repair or replacement with a dedicated supervisor on-site the entire time.' },
            { n: '06', title: 'Final Walkthrough & Warranty Documentation', detail: 'Before we leave, we walk the job with you, confirm everything meets our standard, and hand you your warranty on both materials and labor.' },
          ].map((step, i) => (
            <div class="step-item rounded-xl border overflow-hidden transition-all duration-200" data-active={i === 0 ? 'true' : 'false'}>
              <button class="step-item-btn w-full flex items-center gap-4 px-5 py-4 text-left" aria-expanded={i === 0 ? 'true' : 'false'}>
                <div class="step-circle w-9 h-9 rounded-full flex-shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center font-black text-xs transition-colors">
                  {step.n}
                </div>
                <span class="step-label font-bold text-sm flex-1 transition-colors">{step.title}</span>
                <svg class="step-arrow w-4 h-4 flex-shrink-0 transition-transform duration-200" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/>
                </svg>
              </button>
              <div class={`step-item-body px-5 pb-4 ${i === 0 ? '' : 'hidden'}`}>
                <p class="text-brand-200 text-sm leading-relaxed pl-[52px]">{step.detail}</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===================== GALLERY STRIP ===================== -->
  <div class="grid grid-cols-3 md:grid-cols-6 h-48">
    {[
      '/storm-damage9.webp',
      '/storm-damage3.webp',
      '/storm-damage7.webp',
      '/storm-damage6.webp',
      '/storm-damage5.webp',
      '/storm-damage10.webp',
    ].map((src, i) => (
      <div class="relative overflow-hidden group">
        <img
          src={src}
          alt={`Storm damage repair project ${i + 1} — Central Texas`}
          class="w-full h-full object-cover transition-transform duration-500 group-hover:scale-110"
        />
        <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-brand-900/30 group-hover:bg-brand-900/0 transition-colors duration-300"></div>
      </div>
    ))}
  </div>

  <!-- ===================== TYPES OF STORM DAMAGE ===================== -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-gray-50">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-6xl">

      <div class="flex flex-col lg:flex-row gap-10 items-center mb-14">
        <div class="lg:w-1/2">
          <p class="text-accent-600 font-bold text-sm uppercase tracking-widest mb-3">Storm Damage Types</p>
          <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-black text-brand-900 mb-4">
            Every Type of Storm Damage We Handle
          </h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
            Central Texas weather doesn't pick favorites. We repair all of it.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="lg:w-1/2 grid grid-cols-2 gap-3">
          <img src="/home-repair.webp" alt="Hail damage roof inspection — Central Texas" class="w-full h-40 object-cover rounded-xl shadow-md" />
          <img src="/storm-damage11.webp" alt="Storm damage repair in progress" class="w-full h-40 object-cover rounded-xl shadow-md mt-6" />
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-5">
        {damageTypes.map(item => (
          <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl p-7 shadow-sm border border-gray-100 flex flex-col gap-4">
            <div class="w-11 h-11 rounded-xl bg-accent-600/10 text-accent-600 flex items-center justify-center" set:html={item.icon} />
            <h3 class="font-black text-brand-900 text-lg">{item.title}</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">{item.body}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===================== WHY NOT TO WAIT ===================== -->
  <section class="relative py-24 bg-white overflow-hidden">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-6xl">
      <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-14 items-center">

        <!-- Photo side -->
